oai_dc:dc.dc:title: DEVELOPMENT OF WATER LEVEL CHANGES IN THE GERMAN BIGHT, AN ANALYSIS BASED ON SINGLE VALUE TIME SERIES
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Jensen, Jurgen
Mugge, Hans-Eckart
Schonfeld, Wolfgang
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: German Bight
sea level
sea level rise
single value time series
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Time series of semidiurnal single values of Tidal High Water and Tidal Low Water and their occurrence times from certain tide gauges in the German Bight were evaluated. Detailed analyses were performed to detect district periodicities and changes in the trends not only of water levels but also of the occurrence times by means of mathematical-statistical methods.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 22 (1990): Proceedings of 22nd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Delft, The Netherlands, 1990.
